      ],
      "body": [
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": "Yes. I think I understand. I am not absolutely sure. But what I mean is that it's not the business of the novelist to discuss conscientiously sociology, or psychology, or any techniques we may discuss anywhere. He has to put as much humanity in his work. And if it's sociology or psychology in it, it must be unconscious. You understand what I mean?",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "commenting"
        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": "George Simenon",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "tagging"
        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": "August 4 Panel Discussion",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "tagging"
        }
      ],
      "target": {
        "source": {
          "id": "https://tanyaclement.github.io/harvard1953/august-4-evening-part-three/canvas-1/canvas",
