      ],
      "body": [
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": "It's like Mr. INAUDIBLE who was making prose without knowing it. Everybody makes prose every day. And everybody makes psychology every day, but not the same way that Mr. INAUDIBLE, for example, will start a novel with a trained thought. Today, I will treat the man who did a bad confession to his priest, and then he proved some theory. He proved nothing, and he did always a bad novel. That's what I try to explain.",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "commenting"
        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": "George Simenon",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "tagging"
